					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Here's a super-cheap interface I just built. Works so far at 57600 bps with one serial port I've tested it with. You can of course build both to get bidirectional data transfer. The serial port I tested with outputs about +/-5V signals. The NES-to-PC output only goes down to about -2.6V, which isn't quite to spec, but it works so far. The diodes and transistor are common-variety small-signal.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://blargg.parodius.com/temp/pc_to_nes.png" alt="Image" /> <img src="http://blargg.parodius.com/temp/nes_to_pc.png" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />Mods: please split theFox's question and our exchange after that into a separate thread about PC to NES serial interfaces. Thanks.</div>

