						<div class="postbody">I read that 3% tolerance is common with UART; at 115200 baud on the NES you're you are closer to 4% fast or slow transmitting.. I wonder if this is a significant problem. Timing can be modulated for correct baudrate but the skew would probably throw off the receiver more than the off frequency.
<br />
<br />Here's an output routine for 115200 using 16 cycles / bit (111861 baud):
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">jsr here&nbsp; &nbsp; ;6<br />ldx #9&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;2<br />asl a&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;2 - 10<br />loop:<br />sta $4016&nbsp; &nbsp;;4<br />lsr a&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; ;2<br />sta zpg_garbage ;3<br />sec&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;2<br />dex&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;2<br />bne loop&nbsp; &nbsp; ;3 - 16*9+15<br />rts&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;6 - 175 cc total<br /></div></div>

