				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A big benefit of using serial (even if just a USB-serial adaptor) is that the host-side drivers use a well-worn protocol. You don't have to mess with special drivers or communication models when using serial, so it's easy to port to different operating systems. That's not to say you couldn't have a microcontroller with a USB interface to the PC acting like a serial device, but giving the NES a clocked interface (maybe that was your point). If someone wants to release such a cable for the NES, please do!</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
