					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">i might add in that i've designed a Console &lt;-&gt;USB adapter (~5.5x2.5x3cm box + cables) which uses serial communication with the console and communicates with the computer with a ft232 chip (to make it as robust and cross-platform as possible).
<br />
<br />IIRC it should be able to transceive a byte in ~185 cycles, so it should be possible to make it quite fast. it should also be capable of being interrupted by DPCM every now and then without it interfering with the communication.
<br />
<br />would anyone be interested in such a device?</div>

					
